   "body" : "With Boost 1.78 (installed on my system), I get a compiler error:\r\n\r\n```\r\n./fs.h: In function âfs::path fs::operator+(fs::path, fs::path)â:\r\n./fs.h:91:8: error: no match for âoperator+=â (operand types are âfs::pathâ and âstd::remove_reference<fs::path&>::typeâ {aka âfs::pathâ})\r\n   91 |     p1 += std::move(p2);\r\n      |     ~~~^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt appears that in Boost 1.78, `operator+=` became a template function, and our `path` class which subclasses `boost::filesystem::path::path` no longer has an `operator+=` which will work with it.\r\n\r\nI also opened an issue with boost: https://github.com/boostorg/filesystem/issues/223",
